phase('Modules')
const moduleResults = (await parallel(MODULES.map((m) => () =>
  agent(
    `Make this shared module tenant-aware, BACKWARD-COMPATIBLE. Edit ONLY this file: ${m}

For every exported function that runs SQL against a tenant table:
 - add an OPTIONAL trailing param \`orgId?: OrgId\`.
 - when orgId PRESENT: run via tenantQuery/withTenantConnection/withTenantTransaction + add explicit AND <t>.organization_id = $n on reads / stamp on writes / align string-key joins. If the function calls ANOTHER tenant-SQL helper in this codebase, pass orgId through to it (sibling shared modules are being given an optional trailing orgId in parallel — assume that param exists; if a call doesn't yet accept it, leave it and note in notes).
 - when orgId OMITTED: keep EXISTING behavior BYTE-IDENTICAL (raw pool / executor path) so the many un-migrated callers keep compiling + behaving as today. Do NOT make orgId required. Do NOT edit any caller.
 - if the function takes an existing tx client (executor pattern), add optional orgId and when present \`SELECT set_config('app.current_org',$1,true)\` on that client before writes + add explicit predicates.
 - if a table has NO organization_id column (check docs/tenancy/org-id-coverage.generated.md): scope via its org-bearing PARENT (JOIN + parent.organization_id = $n) when a parent exists; else GUC-wrap only and list it in needsColTables.
 - Drizzle neon-http repos: wrap in withTenantDrizzle(orgId, …) from '@/lib/drizzle/tenant-db' when orgId present.
${PATTERN}
This is shared infra — be exact, idempotent (if already optional-orgId, leave it), preserve all behavior/signatures (only ADD an optional trailing param). Do NOT run whole-repo tsc. Re-read your edits. Return the report.`,
    { label: `mod:${m.split('/').pop()}`, phase: 'Modules', schema: MODULE_SCHEMA },
  ),
))).filter(Boolean)
log(`Modules: ${moduleResults.filter((r) => r && r.changed).length}/${MODULES.length} updated`)

// ── Phase B + C: re-thread routes (with verifier findings) → verify ──────────
phase('Rethread')
const results = await pipeline(
  ISSUE_UNITS,
  (u) => agent(
    `The shared modules these routes delegate to were just made optional-orgId (Phase A). Re-migrate these route files to CLOSE the specific cross-tenant leaks below. Edit ONLY these files:
${u.files.map((f) => '  - ' + f).join('\n')}

VERIFIER FINDINGS to fix (each is a confirmed leak):
${u.findings.map((f) => '  • ' + f).join('\n')}

For each: thread the route's orgId (ctx.organizationId / gate.ctx.organizationId / getCurrentUser()) into the shared-module call that the finding names (those functions now accept an optional trailing orgId), and/or add the org-ownership 404 gate / explicit filter as the finding requires.
${PATTERN}
HARD CONSTRAINTS: edit ONLY the listed files (the shared modules were handled in Phase A — do NOT edit them; if a finding names a module function that still lacks an orgId param, pass orgId anyway and note it in stillOpen). Session-less routes (webhooks/sync with no ctx) — resolve org from the payload/USAV transitional or leave + note. Preserve all behavior/response shapes. Do NOT run whole-repo tsc. Re-read each edited file. Return the report.`,
    { label: `rethread:${u.key}`, phase: 'Rethread', schema: RETHREAD_SCHEMA },
  ),
  (mig, u) => agent(
    `Adversarially re-verify these route files after the Wave-2 re-thread: ${u.files.join(', ')}.
Original findings were: ${JSON.stringify(u.findings)}
Migrator now reports closed: ${JSON.stringify((mig && mig.leaksClosed) || [])}; still open: ${JSON.stringify((mig && mig.stillOpen) || [])}.
Re-read the CURRENT file contents (and the shared modules they call, read-only) and confirm each original finding is genuinely closed OR is an unavoidable NEEDS-COL-with-no-parent case. Flag any STILL-open cross-tenant leak or any NEW compile error (wrong arg count to a now-optional helper, missing import). Do NOT edit. verdict 'pass' only if no real cross-tenant defect remains.`,
    { label: `verify:${u.key}`, phase: 'Verify', schema: VERIFY_SCHEMA },
  ).then((verify) => ({ unit: u.key, files: u.files, mig, verify })),
)

return {
  modules: moduleResults,
  issueUnits: ISSUE_UNITS.length,
  results: results.filter(Boolean),
}
